# Legacy Version Resources

While this Modpack Dev Knowledgebase does not necessarily support Minecraft versions below 1.20.1, we are aware of resources for legacy packdev (particularly 1.12.2) that would be useful for anyone making a modpack on those versions! If you develop on older versions, we recommend that you check out these resources, as the rest of this wiki's contents and guides are widely inapplicable to legacy packdev.

* [1.12.2 Master Doc](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1ywofV3ZTGyFcV2IMTaCSczXb6w9fMIVuNlC68QsZ_E8) - Compilation of Discord servers, sites, mod lists, tutorials, and other resources tailored towards 1.12.2
* [Modernized 1.12](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1UxXKZL6VM1y7t7XErz7cUEXX0JEJ_ntFB7A-NdE8Prk) - Template modpack featuring performance, content, and QoL mods
* [1.12 Coalition](https://discord.gg/bj6FXsRjtp) - Discord community centered around developing 1.12.2 mods and modpacks